1
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:06,836
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A MAN WHO DIED.

2
00:00:06,836 --> 00:00:10,636
THE MAN TRIED TO KEEP SPINNING
HIS STORY EVEN AFTER HIS DEATH,

3
00:00:10,636 --> 00:00:13,436
BUT THE STORY
JUST WOULDN'T MOVE ALONG.

4
00:00:13,436 --> 00:00:16,370
FRUSTRATED,
THE MAN LOST HIS PATIENCE

5
00:00:16,370 --> 00:00:19,203
AND CALLED A DUCK
INTO THE STORY.

6
00:00:19,203 --> 00:00:21,936
THE LITTLE DUCK TRIED HER BEST
FOR THE PRINCE.

7
00:00:21,936 --> 00:00:24,403
SHE TRANSCENDED
HER STANDING IN THE WORLD

8
00:00:24,403 --> 00:00:26,736
AND CAME TO LOVE THE PRINCE.

9
00:00:26,736 --> 00:00:29,236
HOWEVER, SHE WAS ONLY A DUCK.

10
00:00:29,236 --> 00:00:31,103
SHE WAS FATED TO SOMEDAY

11
00:00:31,103 --> 00:00:34,103
TURN INTO A SPECK OF LIGHT
AND VANISH.

12
00:00:34,103 --> 00:00:37,070
YES, THAT WAS
THE TEAR-JERKING ENDING

13
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:40,236
THE STORY HAD DECIDED ON.

14
00:00:40,236 --> 00:00:43,270
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

15
00:00:54,436 --> 00:00:57,470
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

16
00:02:30,345 --> 00:02:33,012
-AND SO,
THE PRINCE AND THE PRINCESS

17
00:02:33,012 --> 00:02:35,845
LIVED HAPPILY EVER -- HAPPILY?

18
00:02:35,845 --> 00:02:39,312
HAPPINESS IN THE STORIES
IS, AT MOST, A TRIFLING MATTER

19
00:02:39,312 --> 00:02:43,312
OF A COUPLE OF LINES AT THE END,
THE EPITOME OF BOREDOM.

20
00:02:43,312 --> 00:02:47,145
NO, SHOW ME
A MAGNIFICENT TRAGEDY --

21
00:02:47,145 --> 00:02:50,812
A CATACLYSM OF TEARS FROM WHICH
NOT ONE OF THE PLAYERS IS SAVED

22
00:02:50,812 --> 00:02:53,578
AND TO WHICH
A HAPPY ENDING NEVER COMES.

23
00:02:53,578 --> 00:02:56,078
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

24
00:02:56,078 --> 00:02:59,612
CONGRATULATIONS.

25
00:02:59,612 --> 00:03:03,112
-PRINCE, WHAT DO YOU HOPE
TO DO AT THIS POINT?

26
00:03:03,112 --> 00:03:06,512
DOES IT NOT MATTER TO YOU
WHAT HAPPENS TO THE GIRL

27
00:03:06,512 --> 00:03:08,978
SINKING INTO DESPAIR
INSIDE OF ME?

28
00:03:08,978 --> 00:03:12,145
-I WILL SAVE THE PRINCESS,
NO MATTER WHAT.

29
00:03:12,145 --> 00:03:13,312
-QUACK!

30
00:03:13,312 --> 00:03:15,945
-YOU MEAN TO TELL ME
IT'S YOUR INTENTION

31
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:19,512
TO TAKE A HUMAN GIRL RAISED
ON MY BLOOD AS YOUR PRINCESS?

32
00:03:19,512 --> 00:03:21,245
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-MYTHO!

33
00:03:21,245 --> 00:03:23,912
-MYTHO, ARE YOU --

34
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:26,412
-[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

35
00:03:26,412 --> 00:03:29,245
YOU FOOL!

36
00:03:29,245 --> 00:03:32,278
[ CROWS CAWING ]

37
00:03:35,212 --> 00:03:38,212
REMEMBER,
THOSE CROWS WERE ONCE PEOPLE.

38
00:03:38,212 --> 00:03:42,345
WOULD YOU RAISE YOUR SWORD
AGAINST THEM, PRINCE?

39
00:03:42,345 --> 00:03:44,612
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]

40
00:03:44,612 --> 00:03:47,112
-WHAT WILL YOU DO, MYTHO?

41
00:03:47,112 --> 00:03:51,945
-CROWS, DELIVER THE HEART
OF THE PRINCE UNTO ME.

42
00:03:51,945 --> 00:03:53,778
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

43
