GIVE US YOUR HEART!

45
00:03:56,512 --> 00:03:57,912
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

46
00:03:57,912 --> 00:03:59,278
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

47
00:03:59,278 --> 00:04:02,778
-CURSED RAVEN,
YOUR CRUELTY KNOWS NO END.

48
00:04:02,778 --> 00:04:04,478
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

49
00:04:04,478 --> 00:04:06,078
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

50
00:04:06,078 --> 00:04:07,912
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

51
00:04:07,912 --> 00:04:09,845
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

52
00:04:09,845 --> 00:04:11,712
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

53
00:04:11,712 --> 00:04:13,578
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

54
00:04:13,578 --> 00:04:14,978
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

55
00:04:14,978 --> 00:04:16,978
-QUACK!
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

56
00:04:16,978 --> 00:04:19,312
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

57
00:04:19,312 --> 00:04:21,145
GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-QUACK!

58
00:04:21,145 --> 00:04:23,745
[ SCREAMING ]

59
00:04:31,045 --> 00:04:32,412
-[ GASPS ]
-MYTHO!

60
00:04:32,412 --> 00:04:35,045
-[ GRUNTING ]

61
00:04:39,478 --> 00:04:41,945
-GIVE ME YOUR HEART!

62
00:04:41,945 --> 00:04:44,212
-GIVE ME YOUR HEART! AAH! AAH!

63
00:04:44,212 --> 00:04:46,312
-[ Echoing ] HEART!

64
00:04:46,312 --> 00:04:47,645
-[ GROANS ]

65
00:04:47,645 --> 00:04:50,245
-[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

66
00:04:50,245 --> 00:04:51,745
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

67
00:04:51,745 --> 00:04:53,145
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

68
00:04:53,145 --> 00:04:54,578
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

69
00:04:54,578 --> 00:04:56,278
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

70
00:04:56,278 --> 00:04:57,945
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

71
00:04:57,945 --> 00:05:00,012
GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-[ SIGHS ]

72
00:05:00,012 --> 00:05:01,545
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

73
00:05:01,545 --> 00:05:02,978
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

74
00:05:02,978 --> 00:05:04,445
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

75
00:05:04,445 --> 00:05:05,945
-MYTHO!

76
00:05:05,945 --> 00:05:08,378
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

77
00:05:08,378 --> 00:05:10,045
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

78
00:05:10,045 --> 00:05:11,712
-STOP THIS NOW!
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

79
00:05:11,712 --> 00:05:13,712
GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-QUACK!

80
00:05:13,712 --> 00:05:15,812
-DUCK, WHAT --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

81
00:05:15,812 --> 00:05:18,512
-QUACK!
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

82
00:05:18,512 --> 00:05:20,878
GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-I SAID STOP!

83
00:05:20,878 --> 00:05:24,045
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-WE HAVE TO HELP MYTHO!

84
00:05:24,045 --> 00:05:25,278
-DUCK.

85
00:05:25,278 --> 00:05:27,345
"THE DUCK FLAPPED
WITH ALL HER STRENGTH,

86
00:05:27,345 --> 00:05:29,212
"HURRYING TO THE SIDE
OF THE PRINCE.

87
00:05:29,212 --> 00:05:31,645
"AS IF IT HAD
SENSED HER FEELINGS,

88
00:05:31,645 --> 00:05:33,712
A GUST OF WIND CAME TO HER AID."

89
00:05:33,712 --> 00:05:34,912
-GIVE US YOUR HEART!

90
00:05:34,912 --> 00:05:36,045
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

91
00:05:36,045 --> 00:05:37,878
GIVE US YOUR HEART!

92
00:05:37,878 --> 00:05:39,545
GIVE US YOUR HEART!
-STOP IT!

93
00:05:39,545 --> 00:05:41,612
[ CROWS GASP ]
-QUACK?

94
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:43,978
-[ SCREAMING ]
-[ GASPS ]

95
00:05:43,978 --> 00:05:45,545
-[ GROANS ]

96
00:05:45,545 --> 00:05:46,712
[ CROWS CAWING ]

97
00:05:46,712 --> 00:05:48,512
-QUACK!
-[ GASPS ]

98
00:05:48,512 --> 00:05:50,178
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]
-[ GROANING ]

99
00:05:50,178 --> 00:05:53,512
-"THE CROWS' RELENTLESS ATTACKS
ON THE DUCK...

100
00:05:53,512 --> 00:05:58,278
"ST...ST...ST...

101
00:05:58,278 --> 00:06:00,478
STILL KEPT GOING."

102
00:06:00,478 --> 00:06:02,745
-[ GROANS ]
-[ GASPS ]

103
00:06:08,778 --> 00:06:10,378
-DUCK!

104
00:06:10,378 --> 00:06:11,912
-HEY! WAIT!

105
00:06:11,912 --> 00:06:13,012
-[ GROANS ] MOVE IT!

106
00:06:13,012 --> 00:06:14,278
I HAVE TO GO.
-AND WHAT WILL YOU DO?

107
00:06:14,278 --> 00:06:16,445
YOU SAID YOURSELF
THAT YOU WERE USELESS

108
00:06:16,445 --> 00:06:18,045
TO PROTECT ANYONE AS A KNIGHT.

109
00:06:18,045 --> 00:06:19,912
YOU'LL JUST END UP
DYING IN VAIN.

110
00:06:19,912 --> 00:06:21,178
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

111
00:06:21,178 --> 00:06:23,312
YOU DECIDED TO WRITE A STORY,
DIDN'T YOU?

112
00:06:23,312 --> 00:06:25,345
THEN WRITE IT TO THE END.
CONCENTRATE.

113
00:06:25,345 --> 00:06:27,345
ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?

114
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:29,612
-DAMN IT.

115
00:06:29,612 --> 00:06:31,612
-[ GASPS ]

116
00:06:31,612 --> 00:06:33,612
SOMEONE'S COMING, ZURA.

117
00:06:33,612 --> 00:06:35,245
-[ SIGHS ]

118
00:06:35,245 --> 00:06:37,245
-WAIT. ISN'T THAT...?

119
00:06:37,245 --> 00:06:39,712
[ CHAINS CLINKING ]

120
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:45,312
GET INSIDE.

121
00:06:45,312 --> 00:06:47,612
-OH!

122
00:06:50,378 --> 00:06:51,645
-QUACK.

123
00:06:51,645 --> 00:06:55,145
-YOUR HEART!

124
00:06:55,145 --> 00:06:58,412
YOUR HEART!

125
00:06:58,412 --> 00:07:02,278
YOUR HEART!

126
00:07:02,278 --> 00:07:03,778
-QUACK! QUACK!

127
00:07:03,778 --> 00:07:06,778
-YOUR HEART!
-QUACK!

128
00:07:06,778 --> 00:07:09,145
PLEASE, STOP IT!

129
00:07:09,145 --> 00:07:10,612
-YOUR HEART!

130
00:07:10,612 --> 00:07:12,778
-[ Thinking ]
AT THIS RATE -- AT THIS RATE,

131
00:07:12,778 --> 00:07:16,778
I'LL JUST BE LETTING THEM
STEAL MY HEART.

132
00:07:16,778 --> 00:07:21,278
SO I REALLY HAVE NO CHOICE
AFTER ALL BUT TO SEAL HIM AWAY

133
00:07:21,278 --> 00:07:23,645
BY RUNNING MY SWORD
THROUGH MY OWN HEART AGAIN?

134
00:07:23,645 --> 00:07:25,145
-NO.

135
00:07:25,145 --> 00:07:27,845
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT, MYTHO.

136
00:07:27,845 --> 00:07:30,512
DAMN. IS IT TRUE THEN?

137
00:07:30,512 --> 00:07:34,645
DO I REALLY NOT HAVE ENOUGH
POWER TO REWRITE THE STORY?

138
00:07:34,645 --> 00:07:37,312
-BUT THAT DEPENDS ON --
I'M JUST A DUCK.

139
00:07:37,312 --> 00:07:40,645
JUST A DUCK WITH NO POWER.

140
00:07:40,645 --> 00:07:43,045
JUST A DUCK
WHO CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

141
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:45,978
-THAT'S RIGHT,
EVEN THOUGH YOU TRANSCENDED

142
00:07:45,978 --> 00:07:49,312
YOUR DUCK'S PLACE IN THE WORLD
AND TRIED SO HARD.

143
00:07:49,312 --> 00:07:53,145
BUT YOU SEE, UNFORTUNATELY,

144
00:07:53,145 --> 00:07:55,545
THIS STORY WON'T HAVE
A HAPPY ENDING,

145
00:07:55,545 --> 00:07:58,012
NO MATTER HOW HARD
YOU EXERT YOURSELF.

146
00:07:58,012 --> 00:07:59,445
THE MORE YOU STRUGGLE,

147
00:07:59,445 --> 00:08:02,112
THE MORE TRAGIC
IT WILL ULTIMATELY BECOME.

148
00:08:02,112 --> 00:08:03,612
WHY, YOU ASK?

149
00:08:03,612 --> 00:08:05,612
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

150
00:08:05,612 --> 00:08:08,645
WHO OF US CAN TELL?

151
00:08:08,645 --> 00:08:10,845
-I WILL NOT ALLOW YOU

152
00:08:10,845 --> 00:08:14,178
TO LEAD THE STORY
DOWN A PATH TO TRAGEDY.

153
00:08:14,178 --> 00:08:16,478
-FAKIR, ARE YOU JUST
GONNA GIVE UP?

154
00:08:16,478 --> 00:08:18,978
-THAT'S IT.
THERE'S NO OTHER WAY NOW.

155
00:08:18,978 --> 00:08:21,478
-WHAT -- WHAT CAN I DO?

156
00:08:21,478 --> 00:08:24,412
-SINK INTO THE DEPTHS
OF ETERNAL DESPAIR

157
00:08:24,412 --> 00:08:28,012
AS YOU VAINLY DREAM
OF A HAPPY ENDING TO THE STORY.

158
00:08:28,012 --> 00:08:31,445
THE GREATEST TRAGEDY
HAS NO FINALE.

159
00:08:34,278 --> 00:08:36,612
[ CROWS GASP, CAW ]

160
00:08:36,612 --> 00:08:38,645
-[ WHIMPERS, GASPS ]

161
00:08:41,012 --> 00:08:44,012
-HERE AND NOW, I WILL
PIERCE THIS HEART ONCE MORE.

162
00:08:44,012 --> 00:08:45,212
-WHAT?

163
00:08:45,212 --> 00:08:47,112
-THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

164
00:08:47,112 --> 00:08:50,212
IF YOU SEAL ME AWAY,
THE PRINCESS WILL ALSO BE.

165
00:08:50,212 --> 00:08:52,545
-NO MATTER HOW MANY YEARS
MAY PASS,

166
00:08:52,545 --> 00:08:55,212
I VOW I WILL RETURN AGAIN
AND DEFEAT YOU.

167
00:08:55,212 --> 00:08:58,478
ONCE THAT'S DONE, I WILL GO
AND END MY OWN LIFE

168
00:08:58,478 --> 00:09:00,545
AND MEET THE PRINCESS IN HEAVEN.

169
00:09:00,545 --> 00:09:02,212
-NO!

170
00:09:02,212 --> 00:09:04,412
-YOU MEAN YOU'RE GOING
TO LOSE YOUR HEART

171
00:09:04,412 --> 00:09:07,045
AND SUFFER THROUGH THAT
ALL OVER AGAIN?

172
00:09:07,045 --> 00:09:10,378
-AFTER YOU FINALLY GOT
YOUR HEART BACK,

173
00:09:10,378 --> 00:09:12,378
YOU MUSTN'T DO THAT.

174
00:09:12,378 --> 00:09:13,912
YOU MUSTN'T.

175
00:09:13,912 --> 00:09:15,812
YOU MUSTN'T!

176
00:09:34,112 --> 00:09:36,412
YOU MUSTN'T!

177
00:09:36,412 --> 00:09:37,945
-[ GASPS ]
-[ GASPS ]

178
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:39,478
-HMM?

179
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:42,478
-YOU MUSTN'T!
YOU MUSTN'T DO THAT!

180
00:09:42,478 --> 00:09:44,512
MYTHO, PLEASE STOP!

181
00:09:44,512 --> 00:09:45,978
DON'T GIVE UP!

182
00:09:45,978 --> 00:09:47,978
-TUTU.

183
00:09:47,978 --> 00:09:50,312
-DON'T GIVE UP!

184
00:09:50,312 --> 00:09:52,245
-WELL, YOU STILL INTEND

185
00:09:52,245 --> 00:09:54,312
TO RESIST THE FATE
YOU'VE BEEN GIVEN?

186
00:09:54,312 --> 00:10:00,645
-FAKIR, I WANT
TO HELP MYTHO ONE MORE TIME.

187
00:10:00,645 --> 00:10:02,812
-DUCK.

188
00:10:02,812 --> 00:10:05,312
-WHAT'S THAT?
DO MY EARS DECEIVE ME?

189
00:10:05,312 --> 00:10:08,812
A MERE DUCK HELP THE PRINCE?
HOW DELICIOUSLY FUTILE.

190
00:10:08,812 --> 00:10:10,312
-TELL ME.

191
00:10:10,312 --> 00:10:13,478
SINCE YOU ARE NO LONGER
PRINCESS TUTU,

192
00:10:13,478 --> 00:10:16,678
WHAT EXACTLY
DO YOU INTEND TO DO?

193
00:10:20,378 --> 00:10:23,878
-DON'T GIVE UP, EVERYONE.

194
00:10:23,878 --> 00:10:26,445
DON'T LET THEM BEAT YOU.

195
00:10:26,445 --> 00:10:29,245
LET'S GIVE THIS STORY
A HAPPY ENDING.

196
00:10:48,027 --> 00:10:52,627
-THE DEPTHS OF DESPAIR --
I FEEL SO CALM HERE.

197
00:10:52,627 --> 00:10:56,294
NO ONE TO TRICK ME,
NO ONE FOR ME TO RESENT.

198
00:10:56,294 --> 00:10:59,927
THERE'S NOTHING HERE,
NOT EVEN LOVING.

199
00:10:59,927 --> 00:11:03,094
I'LL JUST KEEP DANCING
UNTIL I DIE AWAY.

200
00:11:03,094 --> 00:11:05,927
-[ LAUGHS EVILLY ] THANK YOU.

201
00:11:05,927 --> 00:11:09,194
THE HUMAN GIRL WITH THE BLOOD
OF THE RAVEN FROM THE STORY,

202
00:11:09,194 --> 00:11:11,627
YOUR TRAGEDY HAS LED
THE PERFECT TOUCH --

203
00:11:11,627 --> 00:11:14,260
A LITTLE ADDED FLOURISH
TO MY TALE.

204
00:11:14,260 --> 00:11:16,594
EVEN THOUGH
YOU'D REALIZE THE TOWN

205
00:11:16,594 --> 00:11:18,860
WAS BEING CONTROLLED
BY MY STORY,

206
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:22,060
YOU STILL BELIEVE
THE RAVEN'S FALSE SCENARIO,

207
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:23,727
AND NOW HERE YOU ARE,

208
00:11:23,727 --> 00:11:27,660
GETTING READY TO DIE AWAY
IN THE DEPTHS OF DESPAIR.

209
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:29,660
-[ CRIES ]
-WHAT?

210
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,160
I WOULD'VE THOUGHT YOU HAD

211
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,694
LONG LOST
THE CAPACITY FOR SORROW.

212
00:11:33,694 --> 00:11:35,794
TRAGEDY UPON TRAGEDY.

213
00:11:35,794 --> 00:11:37,027
WELL DONE.

214
00:11:37,027 --> 00:11:39,894
YOU HAVE MY THANKS.

215
00:11:39,894 --> 00:11:42,894
-I KNOW I'M JUST A DUCK.

216
00:11:42,894 --> 00:11:46,727
AND I CAN'T EVEN
PUT ON TOE SHOES.

217
00:11:46,727 --> 00:11:54,060
BUT I FEEL LIKE I CAN DANCE
FOR MYTHO AND RUE AND EVERYONE.

218
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:57,127
FAKIR, HELP ME.

219
00:11:57,127 --> 00:11:58,827
-I'LL TRY, DUCK.

220
00:12:04,994 --> 00:12:08,460
-DANCE WITH ME, EVERYONE.

221
00:12:13,527 --> 00:12:16,994
[ RAVENS CAW ]

222
00:12:16,994 --> 00:12:18,494
-[ GASPS ]

223
00:12:18,494 --> 00:12:22,994
-PRINCE, SAVE THE PRINCESS.

224
00:12:22,994 --> 00:12:25,460
-TUTU.

225
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:30,160
[ CHOIR VOCALIZING ]

226
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:38,960
-LET'S ALL DANCE TOGETHER
AND REMEMBER OUR TRUE SELVES.

227
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,494
-WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU CAN DO?

228
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:44,494
YOU'RE NOTHING BUT A DUCK.

229
00:12:44,494 --> 00:12:47,994
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "WALTZ
OF THE FLOWERS" PLAYING ]

230
00:12:47,994 --> 00:12:50,460
-THE REAL ME IS JUST A DUCK,

231
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:53,994
BUT I CAN STILL DANCE.

232
00:12:53,994 --> 00:12:56,494
SO I SHOULD BE ABLE
TO COMMUNICATE

233
00:12:56,494 --> 00:12:58,960
MY FEELINGS
THROUGH DANCING, TOO.

234
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,960
I WON'T SIT AND DO NOTHING

235
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:03,760
AND THEN DECIDE
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING

236
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:06,960
BECAUSE I'M THE ONE
WHO'S GONNA BE MAKING MY STORY.

237
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:12,460
LET'S ALL GO BACK TO THE REAL
SELVES INSIDE OUR OWN STORIES.

238
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:15,194
LET'S TREASURE OUR OWN FEELINGS,

239
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:18,927
NOT THE ONES THAT SOMEBODY ELSE
HAS CHOSEN FOR US.

240
00:13:18,927 --> 00:13:21,960
[ "WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS"
CONTINUES ]

241
00:13:25,227 --> 00:13:27,494
-IT WAS TRUE THAT HER DANCE
DID NOT POSSESS

242
00:13:27,494 --> 00:13:29,627
THE GRACE AND BEAUTY
OF PRINCESS TUTU'S.

243
00:13:29,627 --> 00:13:34,127
HOWEVER, IT WAS OVERFLOWING
WITH INTENSE, POWERFUL EMOTION

244
00:13:34,127 --> 00:13:35,727
THAT SHONE A WARM LIGHT

245
00:13:35,727 --> 00:13:38,394
ON THE HEARTS
OF ALL THE PEOPLE WHO SAW IT.

246
00:13:40,827 --> 00:13:42,760
-A MERE DUCK.

247
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,994
IF YOU WANT TO DANCE THAT BADLY,

248
00:13:44,994 --> 00:13:49,027
COME DANCE ALL YOU LIKE
IN THE DARKNESS OF DESPAIR.

249
00:13:49,027 --> 00:13:51,760
-CURSED RAVEN! [ GRUNTS ]

250
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,894
-CROWS, DANCE WITH THE DUCK

251
00:13:54,894 --> 00:13:58,360
UNTIL SHE EXHAUSTS HER STRENGTH
AND DIES.

252
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:02,260
[ LAUGHING EVILLY ]

253
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:05,427
[ CROWS CAWING ]

254
00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:06,760
-QUACK!

255
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,260
-COME ON, DUCK.

256
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:11,027
-[ Thinking ] DUCK? I SEE.

257
00:14:11,027 --> 00:14:13,260
SO HE CAN WRITE STORIES
IF THEY ARE ABOUT THAT GIRL.

258
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:14,260
[ CRASH ]
[ GASPS ]

259
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:15,260
-[ GASPS ]

260
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:18,594
-[ GRUNTING ]

261
00:14:18,594 --> 00:14:20,094
-AAH! AAH!

262
00:14:20,094 --> 00:14:21,594
[ GRUNTS ] QUACK!

263
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:22,794
QUACK.

264
00:14:22,794 --> 00:14:24,794
AHH!

265
00:14:24,794 --> 00:14:26,727
QUACK! QUACK!

266
00:14:26,727 --> 00:14:29,327
-TUTU, I WON'T GIVE UP AGAIN.

267
00:14:29,327 --> 00:14:31,227
I WILL SAVE RUE.

268
00:14:31,227 --> 00:14:37,594
THAT'S ANOTHER REASON...
WHY I MUST KILL THE RAVEN.

269
00:14:37,594 --> 00:14:41,594
-[ GROANING ]

270
00:14:41,594 --> 00:14:44,960
-[ SCRIBBLING ]

271
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,594
-QUACK! AHH!

272
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:49,260
[ CROW CAWS ]

273
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:52,594
-WHY CAN'T -- WHY CAN'T I STOP
THESE CROWS FROM HURTING HER?

274
00:14:52,594 --> 00:14:55,094
DAMN IT.

275
00:14:55,094 --> 00:14:56,594
-[ GRUNTS ]
-[ GASPS ]

276
00:14:56,594 --> 00:14:59,394
-[ PANTING ]

277
00:14:59,394 --> 00:15:03,360
-QUACK!

278
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,360
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

279
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,084
-DUCK!

280
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:14,076
-I FOUND YOU, YOU VILE
DESCENDANT OF REPUGNANT HANDS.

281
00:15:14,076 --> 00:15:16,076
-WAIT! LET'S NOT GET VIOLENT.

282
00:15:16,076 --> 00:15:20,076
-THE OTHER BOOKMEN HAVE TURNED
INTO CROWS, LEAVING ONLY ME.

283
00:15:20,076 --> 00:15:21,842
WERE I TO CUT OFF YOUR HANDS,

284
00:15:21,842 --> 00:15:24,076
IT WOULD NOT BE
PUNISHMENT ENOUGH.

285
00:15:24,076 --> 00:15:28,742
-RUE, YOU MUST NOT GIVE IN
TO DESPAIR.

286
00:15:28,742 --> 00:15:31,042
IF MY VOICE REACHES YOU...

287
00:15:31,042 --> 00:15:33,376
-[ GROANS ]

288
00:15:33,376 --> 00:15:36,376
[ CROWS CAWING ]

289
00:15:36,376 --> 00:15:40,076
[ "WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS"
CONTINUES ]

290
00:15:40,076 --> 00:15:42,742
-[ GROANS ] FAKIR IS JUST TRYING
TO END THE STORY.

291
00:15:42,742 --> 00:15:45,609
-TELL HIM TO STOP.
LOOK AT THE TOWN FULL OF CROWS.

292
00:15:45,609 --> 00:15:48,976
DON'T RESIST HIM ANYMORE
WITH YOUR IMMATURE ABILITIES.

293
00:15:48,976 --> 00:15:52,242
THE STORY IS STILL BEING WRITTEN
BY A MIGHTY POWER.

294
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:55,476
ALL IMMATURE EFFORTS WILL DO
IS INVITE UNFORESEEN TRAGEDY.

295
00:15:55,476 --> 00:15:57,309
-[ GASPS ]

296
00:15:57,309 --> 00:16:00,976
-[ GROANING ]

297
00:16:00,976 --> 00:16:03,042
I WON'T GIVE UP.

298
00:16:03,042 --> 00:16:04,876
-COME ON, DUCK.

299
00:16:04,876 --> 00:16:08,042
-FAKIR, I CAN STILL KEEP GOING.

300
00:16:08,042 --> 00:16:13,042
I CAN STILL DANCE.

301
00:16:13,042 --> 00:16:14,542
-ALL RIGHT THEN.

302
00:16:14,542 --> 00:16:16,776
-[ GRUNTS ]

303
00:16:16,776 --> 00:16:18,042
HYAH!
-LOOK OUT!

304
00:16:18,042 --> 00:16:20,776
-[ GROANS ]
-[ GRUNTS ]

305
00:16:20,776 --> 00:16:22,776
FAKIR, WRITE!

306
00:16:22,776 --> 00:16:25,009
-FAKIR'S VOICE DISAPPEARED.

307
00:16:25,009 --> 00:16:26,842
QUACK!
[ CROW CAWS ]

308
00:16:26,842 --> 00:16:29,009
-QUACK!
[ CROW CAWS ]

309
00:16:29,009 --> 00:16:31,276
-FAKIR?

310
00:16:31,276 --> 00:16:33,042
QUACK!

311
00:16:33,042 --> 00:16:35,009
-DUCK.
-FAKIR.

312
00:16:35,009 --> 00:16:37,509
-DAMN IT.
-WHAT HAPPENED?

313
00:16:37,509 --> 00:16:41,342
-WRITE. WRITE FOR THE PERSON
WHO'S WAITING FOR YOUR STORY.

314
00:16:41,342 --> 00:16:44,942
-[ GASPS ]

315
00:16:44,942 --> 00:16:47,042
DUCK.

316
00:16:47,042 --> 00:16:49,142
-IT'S FAKIR'S VOICE.

317
00:16:49,142 --> 00:16:51,842
FAKIR, I CAN STILL...

318
00:16:51,842 --> 00:16:53,509
-"THE DUCK STOOD UP.

319
00:16:53,509 --> 00:16:55,442
"NO MATTER HOW MUCH PAIN
SHE WAS SUFFERING,

320
00:16:55,442 --> 00:16:57,176
"THE DUCK WOULD NOT
STOP HER DANCING.

321
00:16:57,176 --> 00:16:58,976
"SHE WILLED HERSELF
TO KEEP DANCING

322
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:01,776
BECAUSE IT WAS THE ONLY THING
SHE COULD DO AS SHE WAS NOW."

323
00:17:01,776 --> 00:17:03,776
-[ GASPS ] RUE!

324
00:17:03,776 --> 00:17:05,776
[ "WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS"
CONTINUES ]

325
00:17:05,776 --> 00:17:09,276
-DON'T GIVE IN
TO THE RAVEN'S BLOOD.

326
00:17:09,276 --> 00:17:12,909
DON'T BE HELD CAPTIVE
BY DESPAIR.

327
00:17:12,909 --> 00:17:16,242
LET'S GIVE THIS STORY
A HAPPY ENDING.

328
00:17:16,242 --> 00:17:17,842
DON'T GIVE UP.

329
00:17:17,842 --> 00:17:19,276
DON'T BE AFRAID.

330
00:17:19,276 --> 00:17:22,776
[ GROANING ]

331
00:17:22,776 --> 00:17:24,642
-"HER TINY BODY WAS SO WOUNDED

332
00:17:24,642 --> 00:17:27,276
"THAT SHE COULDN'T EVEN
STAY ON HER FEET.

333
00:17:27,276 --> 00:17:31,376
"AND YET, IN ORDER TO GUIDE
THE PRINCE AND EVERYBODY ELSE

334
00:17:31,376 --> 00:17:34,242
"FROM DARK DESPAIR
TO A HAPPY ENDING,

335
00:17:34,242 --> 00:17:36,776
"THE DUCK DANCED ON AND ON,

336
00:17:36,776 --> 00:17:41,242
DISREGARDING THE PAIN,
NEVER LOSING HOPE."

337
00:17:44,276 --> 00:17:47,042
[ CROWS CAW, SQUAWK ]

338
00:17:47,042 --> 00:17:50,442
-"THE POWER FLOWED OUT FROM
DEEP WITHIN THE DUCK'S BODY,

339
00:17:50,442 --> 00:17:54,542
UNQUENCHABLE AND INEXHAUSTIBLE."

340
00:17:54,542 --> 00:17:56,409
-[ GASPS ] WHAT IS THAT?

341
00:17:56,409 --> 00:17:58,409
IS THAT THE LIGHT?

342
00:17:58,409 --> 00:17:59,676
THAT'S RIGHT.

343
00:17:59,676 --> 00:18:01,609
IT'S THE LIGHT THAT ALWAYS
BURNED IN MY BREAST

344
00:18:01,609 --> 00:18:03,409
WHEN I THOUGHT OF TUTU.

345
00:18:03,409 --> 00:18:07,109
-"ONE BY ONE, THAT POWER
WARMED THE PEOPLE'S HEARTS,

346
00:18:07,109 --> 00:18:09,509
"WHICH HAD BEEN FROZEN
BY THE RAVEN'S BLOOD.

347
00:18:09,509 --> 00:18:12,409
"THAT POWER WAS...

348
00:18:12,409 --> 00:18:13,909
-HOPE.

349
00:18:13,909 --> 00:18:16,409
-[ GROWLS ]
-...HOPE."

350
00:18:16,409 --> 00:18:18,542
-HOPE? THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE!

351
00:18:18,542 --> 00:18:20,409
OHH! WHERE DID IT COME FROM?

352
00:18:20,409 --> 00:18:22,409
-AND MY NAME
IS PRINCE SIEGFRIED.

353
00:18:22,409 --> 00:18:25,909
I CALL THE NAME
OF THE PRINCESS, RUE!

354
00:18:25,909 --> 00:18:28,576
-THE PRINCE'S VOICE?

355
00:18:28,576 --> 00:18:30,409
I'M DOWN HERE.

356
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:31,742
-AH!

357
00:18:31,742 --> 00:18:33,242
-WHAT?

358
00:18:33,242 --> 00:18:34,909
[ GASPS ]

359
00:18:34,909 --> 00:18:37,076
[ "WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS" STOPS ]

360
00:18:37,076 --> 00:18:38,609
[ WINGS FLAPPING ]

361
00:18:43,309 --> 00:18:44,976
-[ GASPS ]

362
00:18:44,976 --> 00:18:47,476
-RUE, I'VE COME FOR YOU.

363
00:18:47,476 --> 00:18:49,976
-MY PRINCE.

364
00:18:49,976 --> 00:18:54,076
-LET'S DEFEAT THE RAVEN.

365
00:18:54,076 --> 00:18:55,809
-[ GROWLS ]

366
00:18:55,809 --> 00:18:57,476
[ "WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS"
RESUMES ]

367
00:18:57,476 --> 00:18:59,642
-[ GASPS ]

368
00:19:01,676 --> 00:19:04,176
-MYTHO, RUE.

369
00:19:04,176 --> 00:19:05,642
-MYTHO.

370
00:19:08,676 --> 00:19:13,676
[ GROANING, MOANING ]

371
00:19:13,676 --> 00:19:15,176
-[ SIGHS ]
-[ SIGHS ]

372
00:19:15,176 --> 00:19:18,009
[ GROANING, MOANING CONTINUES ]

373
00:19:18,009 --> 00:19:21,476
[ TWINKLE ]

374
00:19:21,476 --> 00:19:23,476
-[ SIGHS ]

375
00:19:23,476 --> 00:19:24,976
HERE WE GO.

376
00:19:24,976 --> 00:19:26,476
[ PULSATING ]

377
00:19:26,476 --> 00:19:28,209
-YES.

378
00:19:32,409 --> 00:19:34,242
-THE STORY WILL END.

379
00:19:34,242 --> 00:19:35,742
-AH!

380
00:19:35,742 --> 00:19:37,576
-WHAT?! IT'S ENDING?

381
00:19:40,109 --> 00:19:42,142
-[ SCREAMING ]

382
00:19:46,109 --> 00:19:48,842
[ SCREAMING FADES ]

383
00:19:48,842 --> 00:19:50,042
-[ GASPS ]

384
00:19:50,042 --> 00:19:53,842
MYTHO! RUE!

385
00:19:53,842 --> 00:19:56,542
I'M SO...GLAD.

386
00:19:56,542 --> 00:19:59,409
-NO! DUCK! [ GASPS ]

387
00:19:59,409 --> 00:20:03,109
[ TWINKLING ]

388
00:20:03,176 --> 00:20:05,176
-HMM?
-HUH?

389
00:20:05,176 --> 00:20:07,142
-[ MEOWS ]

390
00:20:15,776 --> 00:20:17,709
-I KNOW
WHERE THE STORY IS, ZURA.

391
00:20:17,709 --> 00:20:21,176
IT'S THIS WAY, ZURA.

392
00:20:21,176 --> 00:20:23,176
I'M BACK, ZURA.

393
00:20:23,176 --> 00:20:25,509
-WELCOME BACK
TO THE STORY, PRINCE.

394
00:20:25,509 --> 00:20:29,009
THE ENTRANCE IS THIS WAY.

395
00:20:29,009 --> 00:20:31,976
-AH!

396
00:20:31,976 --> 00:20:33,642
-[ GASPS ]

397
00:20:33,642 --> 00:20:36,476
-WHAT'S THIS? HERE, ZURA.

398
00:20:36,476 --> 00:20:37,842
-I SEE.

399
00:20:37,842 --> 00:20:40,776
EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
IN GOLD CROWN TOWN

400
00:20:40,776 --> 00:20:44,142
THIS THING WAS RECORDING
AS A STORY --

401
00:20:44,142 --> 00:20:46,076
A MECHANISM THAT GIVES BIRTH

402
00:20:46,076 --> 00:20:48,642
TO THE TRAGEDY
DROSSELMEYER ENJOYS.

403
00:20:48,642 --> 00:20:50,742
-TRAGEDY.

404
00:20:50,742 --> 00:20:52,142
HUH?

405
00:20:52,142 --> 00:20:54,942
-FAKIR, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

406
00:20:54,942 --> 00:20:57,276
-I WILL WRITE THE REST.
-WHAT?

407
00:20:57,276 --> 00:21:00,409
-THE PRINCE CAN LIVE
FREELY AS HE PLEASES.

408
00:21:00,409 --> 00:21:01,609
-AH.

409
00:21:05,776 --> 00:21:07,642
RUE.
-YES?

410
00:21:07,642 --> 00:21:12,376
-I WANT YOU TO COME WITH ME
INTO THE STORY AS MY PRINCESS.

411
00:21:12,376 --> 00:21:16,642
-BUT I -- I HAVE THE RAVEN'S
BLOOD INSIDE OF ME.

412
00:21:16,642 --> 00:21:18,809
-RAVEN'S BLOOD --

413
00:21:18,809 --> 00:21:21,642
I WONDER IF IT'S STILL
RUNNING INSIDE MY VEINS AS WELL.

414
00:21:21,642 --> 00:21:22,842
-PRINCE.

415
00:21:22,842 --> 00:21:24,876
-FAKIR, ACCORDING TO THE STORY,

416
00:21:24,876 --> 00:21:28,576
I'M SUPPOSED TO LOVE EVERYONE,
BUT -- BUT RIGHT NOW, I...

417
00:21:28,576 --> 00:21:33,142
RIGHT NOW I SIMPLY WANT TO LOVE
RUE THE MOST OUT OF ANYONE.

418
00:21:33,142 --> 00:21:34,976
-[ GASPS ]

419
00:21:34,976 --> 00:21:38,376
[ CRIES ]

420
00:21:38,376 --> 00:21:39,609
-RUE?

421
00:21:39,609 --> 00:21:42,109
-IDIOT. WHAT'S WRONG WITH THAT?

422
00:21:42,109 --> 00:21:44,076
-I'M SO GLAD.

423
00:21:48,376 --> 00:21:49,709
-YOU'RE DUCK, AREN'T YOU?

424
00:21:49,709 --> 00:21:51,009
-QUACK.

425
00:21:51,009 --> 00:21:53,909
-I TRULY AM GLAD
I GOT TO MEET YOU.

426
00:21:53,909 --> 00:21:55,742
THANK YOU.
-QUACK.

427
00:21:55,742 --> 00:21:57,742
-I LOVE YOU, DUCK.

428
00:21:57,742 --> 00:22:00,609
-I LOVE YOU, TOO, RUE.

429
00:22:00,609 --> 00:22:04,276
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ]

430
00:22:04,276 --> 00:22:06,942
[ BELL TOLLING ]

431
00:22:06,942 --> 00:22:10,809
-AH! THIS IS LOVEY-DOVEY, ZURA.

432
00:22:10,809 --> 00:22:13,609
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

433
00:22:13,609 --> 00:22:18,109
-THANK YOU, TUTU, FAKIR.

434
00:22:18,109 --> 00:22:22,042
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A MAN WHO DIED.

435
00:22:22,042 --> 00:22:26,642
THE FINAL STORY HE SPUN WAS
GOING TO BE A BRILLIANT TRAGEDY.

436
00:22:26,642 --> 00:22:31,642
HOWEVER, THE STORY HAD
AN UNEXPECTED HAPPY ENDING,

437
00:22:31,642 --> 00:22:34,109
AND IT WAS TRIGGERED BY ONE DUCK

438
00:22:34,109 --> 00:22:38,109
THAT THE MAN HIMSELF
HAD CALLED INTO THE TALE.

439
00:22:38,109 --> 00:22:40,109
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

440
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:41,942
-HUH?
-HUH?

441
00:22:41,942 --> 00:22:43,109
-OH!
-OH!

442
00:22:43,109 --> 00:22:46,076
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

443
00:22:49,109 --> 00:22:51,109
-COULD YOU PLEASE BE QUIET?!

444
00:22:51,109 --> 00:22:53,642
[ CATS MEOWING ]

445
00:23:06,209 --> 00:23:09,876
-TO THINK A MERE DUCK
HAD THAT MUCH HOPE.

446
00:23:09,876 --> 00:23:12,309
MY BEAUTIFUL TRAGEDY IS RUINED.

447
00:23:12,309 --> 00:23:16,076
I NEVER DREAMED
THE CHARACTERS INSIDE THE STORY

448
00:23:16,076 --> 00:23:19,109
WOULD BE ABLE
TO CHANGE THE STORY THEMSELVES.

449
00:23:19,109 --> 00:23:21,742
WAIT, WHAT IF IT HAPPENS
THAT ALL THIS TIME

450
00:23:21,742 --> 00:23:24,542
I'VE BEEN A CHARACTER
IN SOMEONE'S STORY, TOO?

451
00:23:24,542 --> 00:23:28,109
OH, WELL, EVEN IF I AM,
I'LL JUST DO WHAT I WANT.

452
00:23:28,109 --> 00:23:30,576
HUH? OH, UZURA, YOU'RE HERE.

453
00:23:30,576 --> 00:23:32,042
THIS STORY IS OVER.

454
00:23:32,042 --> 00:23:33,909
YOU CAN'T STAY OVER THERE.

455
00:23:33,909 --> 00:23:37,709
NOW, WHY DON'T WE GO
TO ANOTHER STORY?

456
00:23:37,709 --> 00:23:39,276
-AH!

457
00:23:39,276 --> 00:23:41,876
-THIS TIME,
ACTUALLY BE USEFUL TO ME.

458
00:23:41,876 --> 00:23:43,709
-I DON'T GET IT, ZURA.

459
00:23:43,709 --> 00:23:45,742
-[ LAUGHS ]

460
00:23:49,442 --> 00:23:55,076
-AND THERE WAS ANOTHER MAN
WHO BEGAN WRITING A STORY.

461
00:23:55,076 --> 00:24:00,276
THAT STORY, FULL OF HOPE,
HAS ONLY JUST BEGUN.

